HEADWORD: zygote
<hw>zy"gote</hw> <pr>(z⟦imac⟧"g⟦omac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
cell resulting from the union of an ovum and a spermatozoon, or
(broadly) the developing new organism arising from such a
cell.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fertilized cell.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>zygotene</ent>⟦br⟧
